post_text:
Principal's Letter will be released on Tuesday, September 8th.

Incoming Freshman orientations will be in-person the week of September 8th - 11th for students only. Students/families have received a scheduled date and time for their orientation. The presentation will be approximately two (2) hours. We ask parents/guardians to drop-off and pick-up in the main parking lot approximately 15 minutes prior to the start time.

Dr. Larkin and Mr. Pimental will hold a virtual Information and Q&A sessions for Freshmen Parents. To assist with parent schedules, there will be two sessions and parents are encouraged to attend one of sessions on Tuesday, September 15th at either 10:00 a.m. or 6:00 p.m.

All Sophomore, Junior, and Senior GNBVT families and students are invited to a school-wide virtual orientation. To assist with parent schedules, there will be two sessions and parents are encouraged to attend one of the sessions on either Thursday, September 10th or Monday, September 14th both at 6:00 p.m.

Links to these orientations have been emailed to GNBVT families.

post_text: #GNBVTalumni
shared_text:
Southcoast Health
July 28 at 12:00 PM ¬∑

Jessica Dodge, RN was a Greater New Bedford Regional Vocational Technical High School student when she earned her Certified Nursing Assistant (CNA) license.

She took her education a step further by pursuing her Bachelor of Science in Nursing (BSN) degree through the UMass Dartmouth College of Nursing and Health Sciences.

Her Freshman year she began working in St. Luke's Progressive Care Unit (PCU) as a CNA where she worked for three years.

After passing The National Council Licensure Examination (NCLEX-RN¬Æ exam) Jessica received a position on our Medical Surgical Unit where she has been a nurse since!

"I just made one year here as a nurse last week! I decided to pursue nursing because my mother was a CNA while raising me. She put herself through nursing school and always inspired me to want to help others," says Jessica.

UMass Dartmouth College of Nursing and Health Sciences recognizes Jessica for her service at St. Luke's!

Jessica Dodge, RN was a Greater New Bedford Regional Vocational Technical High School student when she earned her Certified Nursing Assistant (CNA) license.

She took her education a step further by pursuing her Bachelor of Science in Nursing (BSN) degree through the UMass Dartmouth College of Nursing and Health Sciences.

Her Freshman year she began working in St. Luke's Progressive Care Unit (PCU) as a CNA where she worked for three years.

After passing The National Council Licensure Examination (NCLEX-RN¬Æ exam) Jessica received a position on our Medical Surgical Unit where she has been a nurse since!

"I just made one year here as a nurse last week! I decided to pursue nursing because my mother was a CNA while raising me. She put herself through nursing school and always inspired me to want to help others," says Jessica.

UMass Dartmouth College of Nursing and Health Sciences recognizes Jessica for her service at St. Luke's!

Any student-athlete planning on participating in a Fall Sport must complete the registration form below.

This form is separate from the Fall Sports Sign-Up that went out earlier this summer. Please note, the Department of Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE) and Massachusetts Interscholastic Athletic Association (MIAA) have not made any decisions regarding fall sports at this time. We are proceeding with registration at this time, but will be following all state and local guidance before beginning any Fall Sports.

Click the following link to register:

https://www.cognitoforms.com/GNBVocTechHighSchool/fallsportsregistrationform

Please provide the athletic department with a valid physical, by mail to:
GNBVT Athletic Department
1121 Ashley Blvd
New Bedford, MA
02745

Attn: Ryan Methia

Or via email to:
ryan.methia@gnbvt.edu

We are hopeful that we will be able to offer a complete fall sports program to our student-athletes. If you have any questions or concerns in regards to Fall Sports Registration please feel free to reach out to ryan.methia@gnbvt.edu

The talent show at Greater New Bedford Voc-Tech is a long standing Spring tradition in our school community. Due to COVID-19 and school closure, we were unable to host the talent show onsite this year. However, that did not stop Mr. Tim Rodrigues and Mr. Michael Meriano from putting together a virtual talent show! Showcasing the many talents of our students is something our school looks forward to every year, and this year is no exception. The virtual talent show features six talented acts from singing, to playing instruments, and magic.

https://youtu.be/SFlLXIhRMUo

post_text:
Graduation Selection by the Class of 2020

We recently sent out a survey to the seniors of two plans for graduation this year.

Option 1: The school would hold four (4) separate graduation ceremonies that day recognizing each Academy. This plan can only move forward if health guidelines allow for events of 300-400 people as our plan involves both students and two (2) adults to join them. The ceremony would be held outside on the football field as originally planned and we are looking at live streaming capabilities to reach others at home.

Option 2: A drive-through ceremony that will be held at the back of the school grounds at the end of June.

After receiving 460 responses (70.9%), the overwhelming majority voted for Option 1. This is of course under the understanding that either of these options must be compliant with social distancing and health guidelines.

https://www.gnbvt.edu/2020-graduation-survey-results/

post_text:
Any student in need of an application for a work permit should email Mrs. Walsh at heidi.walsh@gnbvt.edu

Applications should be returned to no later than Monday evenings. Ms. Walsh will be in the building completing them on Tuesdays and setting up appointments for you to come to school to get them on Thursdays. Students will be scheduled 15 minutes apart, must bring their own pen and wear a mask, a table will be set up outside.

Please complete and return it to Mrs. Walsh via email along with a copy of your Birth Certificate or passport and respond to the following questions; address, age, gender, eye color, hair color, and any distinguishing facial marks.

GNB Voc-Tech is proud to announce the Top 10 students for the Class of 2020.

These students have exemplified the consistent hard-work and academic / trade dedication that has lead to their current, and future success.

At GNB Voc-Tech we pride ourselves on building students that are skilled, resilient and passionate young adults. This group is a true representation of our goals. They have become artisans. post_text:
GNB Voc-Tech is recognized as a SkillsUSA Gold Chapter of Excellence

The chapter of Excellence program recognizes chapter achievements as they align with the SkillsUSA Framework. To be considered for this award, chapters develop a yearly action plan, using SkillsUSA‚Äôs program of work model. The SkillsUSA framework includes personal, workplace and technical skills. Student members and our chapter advisors invested many hours into this effort.

‚ÄúWe would like to give our sincere appreciation to the Chapter Officers and the other amazing students involved in our school‚Äôs chapter for their contributions to the CEP program,‚Äù Lori Russell-Pelsue, GNBVT‚Äôs Chapter advisor said. Achieving this honor is truly a team effort.
SkillsUSA is dedicated to fostering career and technical skills and ensuring that students are equipped for the world of work. Greater New Bedford Voc-Tech has been affiliated with SkillsUSA for a number of years and is a program that has benefited Greater New Bedford Voc-Tech students for decades.
